to return html pages with flask we use an inbuilt function imported from Flask called render_template()
render_template("nameoffile") \*_the file has to be inside the template folder_

Template inheritance - reducing redudancy in creatin html pages by creating one common html file that defined the structure of every single html file.
---< this file will contain all common componenrs accross all pages >
-Every html file will now inherit the common components from it
-Template inheritance in Flask uses Jinja syntax

{% extends 'base.html' %} --> inherit all common components

Jinja 2 syntax
Jinja is a syntax inbuilt with flask to render Python data

For variables (key features)
--> {{ }} syntax
-->Control structures {% %} \*_Key features of control structures_

POSTING DATA
Workflow - sending resources / requests to a server from a client
e.g Posting a picture on ig

1.Provide a user with a form to insert data
2.User fills the form and submits it --> submitted to a Flask route
--> data coming from the form to the server is sent in key-value pairs

    *name* - attribute used to identify a form element when sending to a server

    Form Checklist
    -< everything a form requires in order to submit a form to Flask>

    action attribute - defines the route where the forms data is to be submitted
    method --->
        *HTTP Methods*
        1. GET - fetching data from a server
        2. POST - sending data / request to a server (inserting products, making sales)
        3. PUT - updating an exsisting resource (changing password, changing product name)
        4. DELETE - getting rid of a resource (deleting a product)

    name
    input type
    button --> submit

3.Flask extracts from data and processses it
flask uses a request object to extract data fromn the form using the key
(comes from the name attribute)
---> request.form - method used to access and extract form data using keys
---> request.method - method used to extract the method using the form

     *import request from flask*

4.Store / insert this data using functions
  --store the data in a tuple
  --import the function to insert and use it
  --the user is redirected

5.A user is redirected
--use redirect function imported from flask
--redirect also takes another function 
in the method ---> redirect(url_for(''))

